## Compiler fail when exporting prop with assignment expression as default value #3386

## Problem
We have unexpected error when svelte parse **declaration assignment**
```let bar = (foo = 1)```

```
Error: TODO this should not happen!
    at dom (/ceres/node_modules/svelte/compiler.js:17865:20)
    at compile (/ceres/node_modules/svelte/compiler.js:23840:16)
    at preprocessPromise.then.code (/ceres/node_modules/rollup-plugin-svelte/index.js:252:22)
    at process._tickCallback (internal/process/next_tick.js:68:7)
```

## Annotaion
Most part of this merge request has been wark with AST while svelte compile. In this description I will talk only about part of code from 'walk function' (**walk**) to '**throw new Error(TODO this should not happen!)**'. Sorry for my english.

## Problem detalization
First of all let me illustrate the svelte default work with assignment expression (pic.1)

Picture 1:
![photo_2019-08-22_04-49-53](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12611926/63479920-ac854900-c498-11e9-9ed1-f7f6bec28cc3.jpg)

### Test №0
```
let foo;
let bar;
bar = (foo = 1);
```

In pic.1 we can see how svelte walk through <script> teg and analysing AST (texts - nodes, arrow - direction, number - walk order). If we look at the code we will see that svelte do all 'significant' action when node **leaving** (remember this). Test №0 work normal because pending_assignments array is empty after svelte walk through AST.

Denote next reductions (more short)

Picture 2:
![photo_2019-08-22_04-49-50](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12611926/63480443-9082a700-c49a-11e9-9df9-a2f312dcc525.jpg)

### Test №1
Now look at the case with error (pic.3)

Picture 3:
![photo_2019-08-22_04-50-13](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12611926/63480484-b4de8380-c49a-11e9-9100-e52662c636e6.jpg)

```
let foo;
let bar = (foo = 1);
```

In code AE and UpdateExpression have option to add some names in pending stack. In this case AE pushed name 'foo' in stack. Then nodes  actions '**leave**' 19,20,21,22 will not resolve values in stack and we have error.

Why like that? look at the source svelte code (code.1) and picture (pic.4) and we will see that **ONLY** Statement-like and AFE nodes have opportunity to refresh entyre pending stack (and they do it always). In Test №1 we don't have nodes with permission to refresh stack. As a result we have error.

Code 1:
```
if (pending_assignments.size > 0) {
	if (node.type === 'ArrowFunctionExpression') {
		const insert = Array.from(pending_assignments).map(name => component.invalidate(name)).join('; ');
		pending_assignments = new Set();

		code.prependRight(node.body.start, `{ const $$result = `);
		code.appendLeft(node.body.end, `; ${insert}; return $$result; }`);

		pending_assignments = new Set();
	}

	else if (/Statement/.test(node.type)) {
		const insert = Array.from(pending_assignments).map(name => component.invalidate(name)).join('; ');

		if (/^(Break|Continue|Return)Statement/.test(node.type)) {
			if (node.argument) {
				code.overwrite(node.start, node.argument.start, `var $$result = `);
				code.appendLeft(node.argument.end, `; ${insert}; return $$result`);
			} else {
				code.prependRight(node.start, `${insert}; `);
			}
		} else if (parent && /(If|For(In|Of)?|While)Statement/.test(parent.type) && node.type !== 'BlockStatement') {
			code.prependRight(node.start, '{ ');
			code.appendLeft(node.end, `${code.original[node.end - 1] === ';' ? '' : ';'} ${insert}; }`);
		} else {
			code.appendLeft(node.end, `${code.original[node.end - 1] === ';' ? '' : ';'} ${insert};`);
		}

		pending_assignments = new Set();
	} else if (parent && parent.type !== 'ForStatement' && node.type === 'VariableDeclaration') {
		const insert = Array.from(pending_assignments).map(name => component.invalidate(name)).join('; ');

		code.appendLeft(node.end, `${code.original[node.end - 1] === ';' ? '' : ';'} ${insert};`);
		pending_assignments = new Set();
	}
}
```
