## Solution
I propose a solution where we share to VDion 'refresh option' of pending stack(VDtoe i rejected by reason below) and add condition to rare declaration assignment in 'for' cycle .

### Test 2

Some time i was spent to find rare cases where refreshing pending stack in VDion will lead to error and i got it. I checked in practice that all nodes from code №0 lead to error when you have declaration assignment, except ForStatement. When svelte 'leave' from VDion node then it trying to add $$invalidate for vars (in some cases).  This incorrect semantically (for JS) and lead to error on all platforms. So I decided to add 'check' of current node parent to exclude case where parents it's ForState and decided use VDion (VDtor parent = VDion). 

But why is it safe? Look at the pic.5 and see that for cycle always have Statements-like nodes like ForStatement and BlockStatement and we have option to process collected names in pending stack when leave from (in this case) 45 or 44. So i don't refresh pending stack in VDion when parent it ForState.

